10. Core Design Logic

The architecture works because it does not trust any single model, prompt, or memory blob.

It separates:

Memory from inference.
Ethics from personality.
Policy from generation.
Identity from session history.
Tools from permission.
Output from validation.

That separation is the whole system.

A model can be replaced.

A session can end.

A memory can be corrected.

A policy can update.

But the continuity kernel remains stable.

The final principle:

Durable AI behavior requires externalized state, explicit constraints, controlled memory writes, validated outputs, and model-independent identity.